vogar

Class ExpectationStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • vogar.ExpectationStore

  • final class ExpectationStore
extends java.lang.Object
    A database of expected outcomes. Entries in this database come in two forms.
    • Outcome expectations name an outcome (or its prefix, such as "java.util"), its expected result, and an optional pattern to match the expected output.
    • Failure expectations include a pattern that may match the output of any outcome. These expectations are useful for hiding failures caused by cross-cutting features that aren't supported.

    If an outcome matches both an outcome expectation and a failure expectation, the outcome expectation will be returned.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public Expectation get(java.lang.String name)
        Finds the expected result for the specified action or outcome name. This returns a value for all names, even if no explicit expectation was set.

      • get

        public Expectation get(Outcome outcome)
        Finds the expected result for the specified outcome after it has completed. Unlike get(), this also takes into account the outcome's output.

        For outcomes that have both a name match and an output match, exact name matches are preferred, then output matches, then inexact name matches.
